I complained to Sprint about my phone suddenly and acutely overheating and becoming very hot to the touch on Saturday. After keeping my phone for an hour, the Sprint technician told me that one of the reasons my phone probably overheated was using FlickFolio because he'd never heard of it.   I told them that didn't seem possible, since I'd used FlickFolio for a month and a half with great results, and I'd enjoyed the app tremendously. But they said that the reason the phone suddenly and acutely started overheating was the fault of this app, one of the only two apps that I ever paid for.  Although I enjoyed this app, I cannot use it anymore, supposedly, because Sprint told me not to. They, then, instructed me never to download *any* apps from google Play Marketplace, and to never load music on my phone, or stream any content at all.  Right.  Edit: It's not fair to the developer of this app that I gave it one star (I was seeking attention). I gave it the five stars it deserves. Since I don't believe Sprint, and I paid for the app, I re-downloaded it.
replyContent: Since you obviously don't believe them, why the 1 star?  I doubt the app is the cause of your overheating.  If you wanted to determine that, you likely could have checked the battery usage to see what app was consuming the most power.  Please contact me, as I'll provide much better support than apparently Sprint.

Its useful but despite having the option selected it refuses to auto upload pictures unless you   a) are charging (despite me telling  it to ignore the charging status)  or  b) physically tell it to upload  I think Ill go back to auto uploading pics to drop box and then upload to flickr at the end of the day  Disappointing but I can live with the loss of £2
App works great on all my device's more than I can say for the official Flickr app.
I love this app! Well worth the money anders works great.
Excellent
Love it

In my opinion not a very good implementation. It does not follow the Android design guidelines and has several missleading settings. Force Sync is also to much hidden in the Settings (should be one button) and did not work on the first try (I excpet things to work on the first try!). Refunded.
Use this for flicker every day
Great app for flickr users
Nice app, easy to use, very intuitive.  Highly recomended!

This is by far the best way to look at Flickr photos on a portable device; organization of the app is terrific, the  photos look great, and it does not crash. It does require quite a lot of internal memory when it downloads photos, but the settings are very flexible so that is not always an issue. Access to your actual flicker account is somewhat limited, but as a photo viewer it is incredibly slick and worth the dough considering the shortcomings of the official Flickr app for Android

I was very happy with this application until the annoying and critical bug with the picture visibility: it just makes once in a while public some of the pictures it uploaded. I often take pictures of documents and upload them to Flickr. I was astonished to find that some of them are practically visible to the whole world. From all the possible bugs this is may be the worst one.
Love it! Only wish is account management but that's unimportant!
Very good app. Thank you.
This is one of the best thing that I have used on my nexus 7. It really is a great source of inspiration for budding photographer's.
A great way to get quality views of flickr on my little phone. Very reliable and improving too.
Mostly better than Flickr's flickr app.

Great app for storing your stream on your phone and tablet.  Once photos are accessed and downloaded, you don't need a connection to access them.  Very quick access to photos makes it easy to find and show photos to friends.
Great offline Flickr cient
I could link to Tapatalk?
Love the smooth full screen, uncluttered view.  Wish adding to favourites was a faster/background process. Plus wish I could see recent activity on my photos.
Puts my Flickr pix at arm's reach, very smooth and well done.
Yeah, FlickFolio! You rock!
The Best, simply!
I like it.it's a nice App

This is the absolute best Flickr experience on my tablet.  The official Flickr app isn't very good and isn't available for tablets anyway, and FlickFolio more than fills the gap.  I love the offline viewing - it makes it very easy to show people my stream or my favorites without needing to be connected to wifi.
Fat better than the Flickr App worth full access to your account and much more!
Please implement reverse chronological sorting within sets. Otherwise the application is great.
I've got five separate Flickr accounts and this app does a great job of helping me stay on top of all of them.
Works great
This is a great app  Has made my flickr account easy to browse on my phone Galaxy y Loads more options too
It's an excellent app for enjoying my photos synched with Flickr.

Love how fast and smooth the program is. Certainly having all my photos backed up on Flickr rather than showing my phone with a billion images.  The only thing that seems odd with this latest version is when scrolling fast to the top of the albums, it seems to bounce you down to the very bottom, which is kind of annoying if you were trying to fast scroll to the top in the first place!
I love the app, but I can't find the "recent activity" link. You know, the one where ppl comment on your photos. Am I missing something here?
Many of the operations mentioned in the feature list (e.g. move, set title etc) only work on single photos, not sets of photos. Auto upload is the only different thing for me. Not worth money
Great app for showing off my Flickr galleries on the go.  One of my goto apps as a semi pro photographer.
A really, really good app.
Works
Why can't I browse a contact's sets?? I don't want to browse just their photostream...
Really impressed with this app. Excellent for browsing photos, works well on a tablet.
Does just what it says on the can :)
Does exactly what I was hoping for
Excellent app. User Friendly and complete.
I really enjoy using this app. Lots of great features and a slick interface. A great tool to showcase your work.
good app
Really nice, fast app.
I've tried several. This one offers every feature I can imagine wanting.

Great app. for Flickr fans. But be careful, it has a "Remove from Favorites" button that lacks a final warning option. I lost two favorites. Gave it three stars due to this weakness. They need to add a final warning or place it as the last selection.
The killer feature in this app is that photos are synced to the phone, so viewing is lightning fast even when wifi and 3g are unavailable.
Can be improved on organizing photos. For viewing photo in offline mode, it is perfect!
Just works as you expect, all our fkickr photo collection is now available offline on my mobile, and tablet.
Well worth the $3. So much better than the actual Flickr app.
Great views and options.   Developer is super responsive.   Thought I had an issue,  turned out to be user error on my part.  Got everything corrected and working great.
In the absence of the stellar flickstackr for Android, this is the best thing going.
Amazing app
Best flickr app for me by far
Been looking for a photo frame slideshow app,  which can turn my nexus 7 into a digital photo frame and use my photos on flickr.  This is it.  Nice interface.  Easy setup.
Initially i had some difficulty getting my photos to upload, but the developer was super helpful in getting me up to speed. Great app and excellent customer service.

There's no way to log off!  I have a few Flickr accounts and can't just log off!  I have to go to my browser and log on to my other account there!  Then I have to refresh every option within FlickFolio to see photos from my new account! Waste of money!
Says I have less than 1gig of space on the SD. I have over 20gig.

I was a bit disappointed when i realized that the official flickr-app wasn't compatible with my Nexus 7, but then i found this app! It really does all the things i was wishing for, and looks good doing it! Great!
Really is the fastest browser that I have used.  But watch your cache.  Several times I find it bloating to gigs of storage and have clear the cache manually.
I wish I could add tags to multiple selected photos. Thanks, love the new update though

Having decided to put my photos on Flickr, an app to display them in a gallery and edit settings without using the website seemed a good idea. So far this is exactly what I need. A fast interface to my Flickr photos.
I use this to easily keep pictures to show from flickr on my phone, works great.
A very convenient way to show a portfolio on today's large display devices. Simple and to the point.
Use this as a portable portfolio which had come in handy for showing clients my work. Works with no issues. Well worth the paltry asking price.
I like this app apart from the fact that it does not seem to support nested collections.
Easy to use. Very useful app.

I really like this app, much better than most. However, I cannot create a new set when uploading photos which seems pretty basic to me (other apps have this). And it would be great if search also showed matching sets or collections.
Would be awesome if i could add a comment to a picture or open a browser to it. Still, decent enough.
Does all that I want it to
Justin Short This is one of the best Flickr apps (much better than the official one) now works brilliantly with ICS- nice work!!

Love all the features and the automatic offline downloads.  I do wish there was a way to manually download the highest resolution version available for an individual photo or collection.  Some times its nice to be able to zoom in with an original.  However that's just a feature request and it's still a great app.
Lets you browse through your sets at amazing speeds. You can find a picture and show it to someone in seconds.

I love this app, it works exactly as it says, and works extremely well. My only request would be an option to increase the number of photos in the "Explore - Contact's Photos" category from 50. I have a lot of contacts who post a lot, and I don't check to often so it's much more difficult for me to check all of their individual accounts. Latest 200 or so would be better.
Quality of application is peerless...  Having my Flickr photos preloaded to my device is great in 3g areas, and the ui is more fluid than 4.0 stock galleries
Easy to use and does what it says on the tin. Perhaps more granularity in what you want to download would be good to avoid space issues.

I only wish there was a way to select which day of interestingness to look at.  I like to browse the explored photos, and would like to look at a specific day.  Other than that wish, the app is very nice.  Works very well on my galaxy tab 2 7.0
This is the most valuable app on my android devices.
Can't speak too highly of this app, it brings access to my entire collection wherever I am. Keep up the good work.
Works well on the Nexus 7, no problems at all but it would be nice to have a two column layout in portrait mode.
I've been using this app on my Sony tablet for a while now and have enjoyed how well the slideshows display.  Also makes uploading to Flickr a breeze.
As a photographer I can now share and show photos right from my nexus 7 with out having to upload them to my device first. This makes using it as portfolio easy & fast!
Excellent way to send my cell phone photos to Flickr, and see all my Flickr photos. Love the ability to assign photos to sets, a well a add titles, descriptions and tags.
Great app particularly good on nexus 7

This was one of the first apps I stuck on my new N7 and it was much better than I was expecting - the N7 instantly became my favourite way to look at photos.  I didn't even ask it to sync my photos and was delighted to discover my entire collection available offline next time I picked up the device....  I've been looking for something as simple and smooth as this for my wife's iPad for the last year and I'm actually scared to show her this app because I know she'll be jealous!  The app makes it really easy to transfer photos to set them as wallpaper, so now my most gorgeous photos make my Nexus 7 smarter-looking than anyone else's! :-)  One star off because it used up 2Gb of my storage without asking me first, but I love the photos so much it's worth it.
great
Works Perfectly with my galaxy note 10.1!!
This works fine on the Nexus 7 and gives flickr users everything they could wish for. I use it daily and recommend it highly
This app makes a great replacement for the official Flickr app, which is not supported on the Nexus 7.
Does what`s supposed to do, as simple as that.

This app displays your images well, especially on a 7 inch tablet. The ui is uninspired but easy to navigate. The only other issue I have come across so far is when trying to add a description to a set I created in app the input field maxes out and you can't see what you are typing anymore.  Basically a good app if you want a quick and elegant way to view your images and don't care too much about much else.

Awesome app Form flickr. Way better than original flickr app. Photos look great in my SGS2 and handling is pure pleasure. It would bei nice to be able to browse other peoples favs as well. Haven't found this option yet.
Just downloaded on my tablet and I love it. The interface is great. The layout is easy to handle. And the app is quick. I love it!

I don't usually leave reviews but this app has quality all over it. Nice fast browsing, great organisation and tonnes of useful settings to customise it. Great to have a usable flicker app for browsing Explore and contact photos, downloading one's pics, and being able to fave and comment from within the app. Great on the Nexus 7. One of the best apps that I've ever used and worth twice the asking price.
Flickr should hire the devs behind this app.  A joy to use. Worth every cent.
It does the job...and it does it very well.  I highly recommend this app.

I was looking for a way to put my Flicker pics onto my tablet. This app did it effortlessly, putting everything into appropriate sets. Downloads while device is charging. Easy to navigate and displays photos full screen. Superb!
Love it for showing off my flicker photos without constantly downloading the same images over and over!
Good app.
Flawless on tablet and phone. A little slow on favouriting but all good otherwise.

I bought this app when it was still quite young. The author has been making gradual improvements and has added loads of excellent features. I use the uploader as well. It has the necessary features, but the UI could use some bulk editing improvements. But, I think they'll be added over time, looking at the way this app has progressed. Worth every penny and more. A must buy for any serious flickr user.
The best flickr app ever found

Lovely on tablet. My only wish is that it would show the uncropped thumbnails in a justified view, alá Flickr Photo Explorer on iPad. Similarly, abilities to go to the original web page and add the image to a gallery would be useful.
Solely for browsing photos, but good app
Excelent but please change the icon
Does everything I need it to.  Great app that allows me to see and upload to my flickr account with ease.
...and there are many.

Amazing app beautifully presented and organized. I'm able to do as much on my tablet as in my PC. Great for finding inspiration while far away from desktop. No issues or handicaps as opposed to other applications. love it!!!
A better way to share to other sites is needed
I bought this because the gallery app on the nexus 7 was very slow as a slideshow and difficult to customise. This is superb.
Much better at uploading (including in batches and automatically) than Flickr's own app. Well worth the price. Now with added custom auto-upload privacy setting!
It works great as an offline gallery for all my Flickr photos. The first sync took a while but didn't require any effort on my behalf. It works well on my Samsung galaxy nexus.
Very nice format and interface.
Best Flickr app
If you are an avid user of Flickr, you have to own this tool.

Great Flickr app
Great app! So much better than Flickr's own which would never connect for me. However, this little beauty is well worth the small price!! Highly recommended!
Super quick and easy way to view and share my photos
Great app

Not only need option to tag photos, but also not all my tags are shown when using tag filter! Excellent program tough.
Works well but there doesn't seem to be a way to add someone as a contact, hence only four stars.  Sony Tablet S & LG Optimus 3D
Upload, browse old uploads etc, looks great. Only thing would be like to be able to do would be upload to more than one set at a time. Oh, and download full sized images.  Otherwise, love it.
Great!!
Great on Sony tablet and easily the best way to view flickr pictures

I love this app and have been using it for awhile to create multiple uploads to Flickr.  However, I just started getting an error message on my Droid X2 about low internal storage issues.  When I did a search through all of my files on the internal storage, Flickfolio is storing EVERYTHING on the internal, thinking the developers might want to rewrite to direct to SD?
A relatively simple app that allows you to cache your Flickr items and view offline. It needed a few kicks to get it fully sync'ed from scratch, but now I'm there all good.
Overall, its a good app. The only thing that is lacking is that, there is no option to download the pictures in original size.

I finally updated the app after buying it months ago and I think it's been vastly improved. Photos now looks sharp on a 10" tablet. Runs very smoothly.   There are still no stats or Recent Activity stream and that's why it's not a 5-star for me.
That's all I got to say... Well worth the money.

While not quite as convenient as using Flickr on a PC, the full screen views and the ability to roll from one picture to the next makes this the best android Flickr app. And being able to use it offline means that I can show people my latest work wherever I am.
Beautiful, and works great!
Simply the best app for viewing your flickr photos. Worth every penny.
Just installed on tf101. Shows pictures perfectly.
Works great on Samsung Galaxy Note. ... In Canada.
Love it

MUCH BETTER.. worth the 2 quid.
After discussed with Brian, I learnt how to configure the app. Works very well.

I love it!

This app brings the convenience and presentation of the tablet to browsing Flickr images, keeping up with your contacts and commenting on photos.  Support is excellent. I had a problem - that turned out to be nothing to so with the app - and the developer went out of his way to sort it out.
By far this is the best app I found for managing my Flickr account on my Motorola Xoom running ICS.
Way better than the official app which I just deleted
Way better than official app
Stable & very useful
Good functionality.  Shame you have to pay for such a simple app, but the pickings were slim.  No way I'm allowing the permissions the official app wants.  Your loss Yahoo.
Good Flickr app.
The best application to follow your contracts and favorites photos on Flickr... Fast and nice.
This is my first android purchase and thanks to you its WORTH it  Please ADD option to reply to person in comments i.e. the reply option on flickr

Excellent app, just what I was looking for. Developer very helpful and answered email within 2 hours.  £2 is an absolute bargain!
I've had it for five minutes and love it. Better than the " real" flickr interface.
Great for viewing pics. Needs an add contact button though.

... the new icon is far too garish and large. And as a previous reviewer's says, its nothing to do with flickr or photos - so the app's purpose is not obvious to any new users.   And these oh so 1970's rounded corners on the sets thumbnails listing page :-(   App used to be simple, very functional and elegant but these tweaks have gone too far. Shame.  Oh and was that clunky, ugly thumb scroller always there? Hides the far r.h.s image on my Galaxy 7" tab, so what about an option to switch it off please?

Love the new icon.!
Everything I've been searching for. Totally worth the money!!
Really does a good job, better than the official app don't regret buying it.
I use it daily and love it.
Best Flickr app out there by far!

Best app that does what it advertises.
Best Flickr application I have found so far on android. Very good for viewing photos. Good updates to, keep em. Coming.
Great app, could do with a sexier icon.
a great app for my Transformer tablet and HTC Rezound
Very nice app.
Great app.  Good functionality and stable.  User interface solid but not on par with top line apps but still great and easy too use.
Developer responded to my queries very quickly. I like this app. It is very useful.
Works like a charm on tablet s.
Great little app.

A frustrating limitation of flickr was the lack of a batch downloader. This app solves that problem beautifully and does all the nit-picky work for me. Works exactly as promised and is a joy to use on my Android ASUS Transformer tablet running 3.2.1.
Awesome.  Exactly what I was looking for.

At points the user friendlyness needs attention. Navigating images is not as easy as it could/should be. For instance: adding a comment to an image opens a popup, but the is no close button. One needs to use the back button at the bottom of the screen. Not very intuitive.
Great app for those that like flickr. Very easy 2 use & covers all the basics

It's odd though: you look at a photo and long press to get menu, then pick "View Favorites". What I wanted was other people who faved THIS pic, and browse their other faves. Instead u just get faves for the person who posted the pic. Bummer

This app is perfect.  The developer answered my email with questions very quickly and he is very open to suggestions (as long as they are reasonable). I can say, this app is worth all of my 299 pennies I spent on it.
This app is really laggy on my phone and my processor is 1GHz.
This app does what flickr should. I love handing my phone over to people so they can see a stream of my latest photos. Great work guys.
Needs the ability to choose the size of photo download
Very good app. Easy and smooth on my xoom tablet. I highly recommend it.
I use this little great app all the time for showing off my Flickr collections to people I meet. The latest addition of pinch zoom, makes it complete.
Since last update, upload is not longer working.
I have tried several apps and thusnis exactly what i was after and i cabt believe how fast it is - excellent and well worth the £1.99
Much better than the others

This is a great app, if you love Flickr it's well worth the money, far better than most other Flickr apps on the market, it does what it say's on the tin . deff one of my MUST have apps.

Looked at quite a few flickr apps and this is the only one that does even half of what I want it to do.  Great... Head and shoulders above the rest.

i just wish it had a widget and pinch to zoom

Outstanding.

Great on phone or tablet.
this is the app I use on a daily basis to upload all my photos to flickr. i'd be very lost without it. [lg ally]

Great app. Works well with my vibrant. Michael
After Chrome & Gmail this is my most used app. It is very slick and presents images perfectly. A great way to get a bit of inspiration.
Really good, so much better than the official Flickr application. Love the ability to sync offline to my tablet. One purchase for multiple devices
This app is getting better, now just missing most recent pictures not just interesting photos, also make adding favorite a liitle faster.
I've been waiting for a great Android Flickr app for a year now, and this one delivers. None of the other free or paid Flickr apps compare.
Love it! Wish I could select multiple photos for upload... :-(

Very disappointed to find that this app does little more than the various free versions on the market. The app description boldly claims "The presentation is very clean for showing clients or family. FlickFolio optimizes photo size for your device", however on my Galaxy S2 I never see anything other than low resolution photos crippled with heavy jpeg artifacting (blocky) and only gets worse when you zoom in. Showing a client one of these photos whilst out and about would be embarrasing, never mind family.
I would find this app a lot more useful if I could change the privacy settings on photos I want to upload.
Very functional, missing a few things you can do on web, or maybe I don't know how, but it sure does a lot of things smoothly.
Best Flickr app out there. However, needs option to auto download when not on charger, (my wifi and charger are in different rooms!)
Amazing app! Perfect way for any Flickr user to showcase their photos. Must have. Syncs and downloads your photo collection to your SD card.
Satisfying user experience so far on mobile as well as tablet.
Fantastic app. Bumped rating from 4 to 5 after search feature was implemented. Any heavy Flickr user should check out this app :)
I don't think any flickr account holder, especially photographers, should be without this app.
Easily the best option I've used to access photos on Flickr from a mobile device.
Just does exactly what it says. Fantastic.

Simple, easy to use and looks great on samsung galaxy s.
Really love the image rendering/quality!
Best flickr app by far!
For whatever reason I needed to install the Opera Mobile Browser to login to Flickr. Once that was done, the app worked flawlessly.
Overall its good,downloads all photos in respected sets. Disappointing-deletes all photos whenever u update the app. I dont understand why!
A simply nice way of interacting with my Flickr. Really love the ability to post things from other apps, then to shared them via other apps. Clean UI.
Best Flickr app available at the moment. Dev actively improving it regularly (don't understand people who complain about too many updates!)
Great app. Download sync works well. Too many incremental updates though.
La mejor aplicacion de flickr en android

I have been looking for something that came close to FlickStackr (great IOS Flickr app). This seems to be closest for what I am looking for (I've tried all the others). My only complaint was the max. number of photos (150) you could access from your favorites. Just this week the developer added an option to increase it to 500 which helped. Thank you! It would be nice to not have a limit at all (maybe in a future release).
I like it. It downloads thumbs quickly and is a nice quick way to go through your sets. Im unable to choose externalSD for downloads on my galaxy2.
Best app for flickr i have found so far, and I have purchased others, not just freebies. I no longer use those. This is my new flickr app!
Great app, but would be useful if you could copy photo urls to the clipboard (for sharing links, rather than copies of photos)
Slick. Much better than navigating the website. An ability to browse for pictures would make this a 5 star app.
Love it, works great! EVO

Nice App, easy to use, and great to have Flickr library available offline.

Honestly the best flickr app on the market well worth the money!

This app is excellent works great on my Galaxy Tab.
Great, but wish it downloaded to normal folder so you can view using default gallery app.
Great app , wish i could create new collections and sets using it.

The best Flickr app available!

The best app, great developer support. Folks, trust this developer to support you if you have problems. He took care of me like no other and stands behind his work, just as advertised. Best Flickr app!

Brilliant, been looking for something like this for ages. Best I've found by far. Lets me view my flickr images offline. Good work!
Just what I was looking for, with the ability to browse by sets and tags, and swipe for prev/next photo. Would like ability to access original size.
